question:
District category contains Wall Street, Single-family Homes, Academic District, and Market District.
Supermarkets category contains Aldi, Grocery Outlet, Fairway Market, and Earth Fare.
The number of each Wall Street 's Earth Fare equals 7.
The number of each Market District 's Aldi equals each Academic District 's Grocery Outlet.
The number of each Academic District 's Grocery Outlet equals 21 more than each Single-family Homes 's Grocery Outlet.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's Grocery Outlet equals 19.
The number of each Wall Street 's Aldi equals 19.
The number of each Academic District 's Fairway Market equals 16 times the sum of each Academic District 's Grocery Outlet and each Single-family Homes 's Earth Fare.
The number of each Academic District 's Aldi equals 9.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's Aldi equals each Academic District 's Fairway Market.
The number of each Market District 's Grocery Outlet equals 3.
The number of each Wall Street 's Grocery Outlet equals the sum of each Wall Street 's Earth Fare and each Single-family Homes 's Grocery Outlet.
The number of each Academic District 's Earth Fare equals 16.
The number of each Market District 's Earth Fare equals 21.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's Earth Fare equals the difference of each Single-family Homes 's Grocery Outlet and each Market District 's Grocery Outlet.
How many Earth Fare does Academic District have?
solution: Define each Academic District 's Earth Fare as a; So a = 16.
